docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2319:# 36. Final Implementation Roadmap Summary
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2323:1. **Build the secure foundation first**: authentication, RBAC, audit, documents, configuration and deployment.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2324:2. **Implement origination and credit controls**: member validation, KYC, application, eligibility, loan limit and appraisal.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2325:3. **Add governance workflow**: sanction approvals, exceptions, conflicts and registers.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2326:4. **Add legal/documentation controls**: templates, signatures, stamp duty, notarisation, checklist and security instruments.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2327:5. **Add financial execution controls**: SAP request, loan account, disbursement readiness, Senior Manager initiation, CFC authorisation and UTR.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2328:6. **Add servicing controls**: repayment, subsidiary deduction, allocation, SAP posting, interest, DPD and MIS.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2329:7. **Complete lifecycle controls**: default, extension, recovery, closure, NOC, security return, archive and compliance trackers.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2330:8. **Harden, test and launch**: reports, exports, regression, UAT, migration, security, operations and hypercare.
docs/source/implementation-roadmap.md:2331:9. **Enhance after stabilisation**: borrower portal, SAP API, bank API, CKYC, bureau, e-sign, CDSL automation and analytics.
docs/source/design-system.md:1:# design-system.md
docs/source/design-system.md:3:# SFPCL Member Credit Administration & Settlement — Detailed Design System
docs/source/design-system.md:5:## 1. Document Control
docs/source/design-system.md:20:## 2. Purpose of This Design System
docs/source/design-system.md:26:1. **No non-member loan processing.** The UI must make member validation visible and enforceable.
docs/source/design-system.md:27:2. **No uncontrolled disbursement.** Disbursement must be blocked until sanction, documentation, SAP setup, bank verification and checklist approvals are complete.
docs/source/design-system.md:28:3. **No invisible exceptions.** Any deviation from limits, policy, required documentation or approval sequence must be visibly captured in an Exception Register flow.
docs/source/design-system.md:29:4. **No unclear accountability.** Every action must identify the actor, role, timestamp, decision, reason and resulting state.
docs/source/design-system.md:30:5. **No fragmented information.** Registers, dashboards and operational queues must be views generated from the same underlying loan record, not separate data islands.
docs/source/design-system.md:31:6. **No borrower-unfriendly communication.** Borrower-facing messages must be simple, respectful, specific and suitable for farmer / FPC contexts.
docs/source/design-system.md:32:7. **No compliance ambiguity.** Legal and regulatory gates must be surfaced through statuses, warnings, checklists, required reason capture and audit trails.
