docs/source/design-system.md:2512:## 46. Success Criteria for the Design System
docs/source/design-system.md:2516:1. Users can identify the current stage and blocker of any loan within five seconds.
docs/source/design-system.md:2517:2. All screens use consistent status, colour, typography and action patterns.
docs/source/design-system.md:2518:3. Approval authority is visible before a user makes a decision.
docs/source/design-system.md:2519:4. Disbursement blockers are unmissable and cannot be bypassed through UI.
docs/source/design-system.md:2520:5. Loan limit calculations are transparent and auditable.
docs/source/design-system.md:2521:6. Documentation completeness is visible before money movement.
docs/source/design-system.md:2522:7. Exceptions are clearly marked across dashboards, loan pages and registers.
docs/source/design-system.md:2523:8. Borrower-facing communication is simple and actionable.
docs/source/design-system.md:2524:9. Internal users can perform high-volume register work without losing clarity.
docs/source/design-system.md:2525:10. Auditors can trace each major decision through documents, approvals and audit logs.
docs/source/design-system.md:2526:11. Designers and engineers can build new screens using reusable patterns instead of inventing new UI.
docs/source/design-system.md:2527:12. Policy changes can be reflected through configuration without redesigning screens.
